  <brief_title>Multiple Sclerosis Rehabilitation Study</brief_title>
  <official_title>'Functioning and Disability' and 'Quality of Life' in an Australian Community Cohort With Multiple Sclerosis.</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Melbourne Health</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Melbourne Health</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The effects of routine rehabilitation in MS patients versus no rehabilitation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Routine rehabilitation inervention in patients with MS. This comprises of medical and nursing
      input, physiotherapy, occupational therapy, speech pathology, neuropsychology, compared with
      a &quot;control&quot; group on the waiting list for rehabilitation intervention. Duration of
      intervention is 6 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
